<TITLE>Jambalaya</TITLE>

<METADATA>
	<SERVINGS>2.5</SERVINGS>
</METADATA>

<COOKWARE>
	<LARGE POT/>
    <LARGE SKILLET/>
</COOKWARE>

<INGREDIENTS>
	<1>
        <ZATARAINS RED BEANS AND RICE MIX>
            <BOX>1</BOX>
        </ZATARAINS RED BEANS AND RICE MIX>

        <CRAWFISH>
            <OZ>12</OZ>
        </CRAWFISH>

        <SAUSAGE>
            <ANDOUILLE SAUSAGE>
                <OZ>12</OZ>
            </ANDOUILLE SAUSAGE>
        </SAUSAGE>

        <ONION>
            <WHITE ONION>
                <QTY>1</QTY>
            </WHITE ONION>
        </ONION>

        <BELL PEPPER>
            <QTY>1</QTY>
        </BELL PEPPER>

        <HASH BROWNS>
            <CUP>1</CUP>
        </HASH BROWNS>
	</1>
	
	<2>
        <OIL>
            <NEUTRAL OIL>
                <OLIVE OIL>
                    <TBSP>1</TBSP>
                </OLIVE OIL>
            </NEUTRAL OIL>
        </OIL>
    </2>

    <3>
        <HOT SAUCE>
            <TABASCO>
                <TBSP>1</TBSP>
            </TABASCO>
        </HOT SAUCE>
	</3>
</INGREDIENTS>

<INSTRUCTIONS>
    <1>
        Slice <SAUSAGE/> into coins. Separate into <LARGE SKILLET/>.
    </1>

    <2>
        Chop <ONION/> and <BELL PEPPER/>. Separate into <LARGE POT/>.
    </2>
    
    <3>
        (a) Sear <SAUSAGE/> over medium heat until browned. Remove and set aside. 

        (b) Sear <BELL PEPPER/> and <ONION/> on medium heat for 9 minutes.

        (c) Separate <HASH BROWNS/> and <OIL/>. 

        (d) Separate <CRAWFISH/>.

        (e) Separate <HOT SAUCE/>.
    </3>

    <4>
        (a) Cook <HASH BROWNS/> and <OIL/> in <LARGE SKILLET/> over medium-high heat. Cook 5 minutes, turn, and cook an additional 5 minutes until golden brown.

        (b) Add a little over 3 quarts of water to <LARGE POT/> for each box of rice. Stir in <ZATARAINS RED BEANS AND RICE MIX/>, <SAUSAGE/>, and <HOT SAUCE/>. Bring to a boil. Cook for 18 minutes, stirring occasionally.
    </4>

    <4>
        Stir in <CRAWFISH/> to <LARGE POT/> and cook an additional 7 minutes.
    </4>

    <5>
        Stir in <HASH BROWNS/> to <LARGE POT/>. Remove from heat.
    </5>
</INSTRUCTIONS>